WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.676
Let's learn about

00:00:01.676 --> 00:00:03.353
Axial skeletion. This

00:00:03.353 --> 00:00:05.030
concept helps us

00:00:05.030 --> 00:00:06.706
understand how the

00:00:06.706 --> 00:00:08.383
world around us

00:00:08.383 --> 00:00:10.059
operates.

00:00:10.059 --> 00:00:11.551
Every big idea

00:00:11.551 --> 00:00:13.043
can be broken

00:00:13.043 --> 00:00:14.535
down into simpler

00:00:14.535 --> 00:00:16.026
parts. We look

00:00:16.026 --> 00:00:17.518
at the core

00:00:17.518 --> 00:00:19.010
principles first.

00:00:19.010 --> 00:00:20.800
In Nigeria, secondary

00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:22.589
schools study these

00:00:22.589 --> 00:00:24.379
ideas to prepare

00:00:24.379 --> 00:00:26.169
students for WAEC

00:00:26.169 --> 00:00:27.959
examinations.

00:00:27.959 --> 00:00:29.715
By understanding this

00:00:29.715 --> 00:00:31.471
topic, you gain

00:00:31.471 --> 00:00:33.227
skills to solve

00:00:33.227 --> 00:00:34.983
real-world problems in

00:00:34.983 --> 00:00:36.739
your community.

